Content Intelligence: Data Engineer		Tumblr		NYC		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Tumblr’s Content Intelligence team is looking for a well-versed engineer and data scientist who’s ready to take over entire features of the code base. You’ll oversee the autonomous agents that sift Tumblr content for patterns and anomalies. You’ll work on the data pipelines that serve candidate lists to administrators, both human and robot.<br /><br /> <strong>What You'll Do:</strong><br /><br /> <ul> <li>Work cutting edge data processing tools to plumb the depths of Tumblr's dataset, seeking patterns that indicate malice and fraud.</li> <li>Propose hypotheses and prove (or disprove!) them with your data models.</li> <li>Optimize queries for time, memory space, and disk I/O. Stress in-memory caches, mappers, reducers, and learning agents to their limit and past it. Learn from the wreckage of your fallen robots.</li> <li>Dream about machine intelligence and build the possible parts.</li> <li>Deliver actionable candidate sets to tool developers through custom interfaces.</li> <li>Write abstracts, talks, and papers about your adventures in data.</li> <li>Collaborate with a talented team of designers and fellow engineers</li> </ul> <br /> <strong>What We’re Looking For:</strong><br /><br /> <ul> <li>A passion for information and architecture.</li> <li>A desire to be deeply involved in product definition, a drive to build the very best data products, and a keen sense for beautiful, pragmatic code.</li> <li>Experience with sites that rely on architecture beyond the basic LAMP stack.</li> <li>A deep understanding of Tumblr’s features.</li> <li>Smarts, humility, and equal willingness to learn and teach.</li> <li>Expert-level knowledge in both scripting languages and query languages.</li> <li>Working knowledge of Javascript, PHP, and HTML.</li> </ul> <br /><strong>Tools We Like:</strong><br /><br /> <ul> <li>PHP5, Ruby, and Scala</li> <li>MySQL</li> <li>Varnish, Redis, Memcached</li> <li>Hadoop, Hive, Pig, Cascading, Scalding</li> <li>Machine learning systems</li> <li>Computer-vision systems</li> <li>Asynchronous requests and queues (frontend and backend)</li> <li>git and GitHub</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Founded by David Karp in New York City in 2007, Tumblr is a microblogging platform that allows users to effortlessly share anything. Tumblr now hosts over 45 million blogs with over 19 billion posts to date. Our pageview to engineer ratio is 1 billion PV per month to 1 engineer. This means every line of code every developer writes has a huge impact. We are focused on building tools and technologies that will advance the state of the art in dealing with massively scaled websites as we quickly grow past 30,000 requests and 1,300 posts per second. We are also excited to deliver a range of new products that will enable users to share their own creative content, discover content, and connect to one another in new ways.</div>